      "content": "That makes sense, I see the issue with the `clear()` call now. I'll look into replacing those raw pointers with `std::unique_ptr` immediately. \n\nBeyond just fixing this specific leak, though, how should I approach finding others in the rest of the codebase? Since this is an embedded system, I don't have the luxury of running heavy Valgrind or AddressSanitizer suites on the target hardware during the actual vehicle tests. What are some lightweight ways to monitor for these kinds of gradual leaks in a resource-constrained environment?",
      "source": "evaluator"
